{
  "texts": [
    "These models will clearly be better at simulating some people over other people, and work better for some applications than others.",
    "Argyle et al.",
    "[4] conclude from this that algorithmic fidelity must be measured anew for each research question.",
    "Determining there is sufficient algorithmic fidelity to address one research question does not imply the same will be true for others [4].",
    "At present, there are still no generally accepted best practices for research on humans using LLMs."
  ]
}